  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Crisis Specific Appeals</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ireland&#x2019;s humanitarian response and funding is directed to where needs are greatest in sudden onset, protracted and conflict related crises, with a particular emphasis on forgotten and underfunded emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under the Crisis Specific Appeals budget line, Ireland will continue to respond to severe, large scale, humanitarian crises around the globe, and in particular in Africa and the Middle East. Further support under this budget line is proposed for crises in the Lake Chad Basin and across the Sahel, building on humanitarian assistance provided since 2016. Ireland will also provide funding to the humanitarian response to the refugee/IDP crisis in Bangladesh and Myanmar.</narrative>
  </description>
